<br /><br>
<h4>GraphQL Test</h4>
<br />
<p>
    This is a quick test of GraphQL using the Hot Chocolate framework.
</p>
<p>
    Further implementations will allow for more searches. For now, it will grab any attributes
    you want from all equipment. This implements a basic data loader to get around the N+1 problem when looking at tags.
</p>
<br /><br />
      <div id="graphql-parameters-container">
          <select id="graphql-selectpicker" class="selectpicker" multiple>
              <option>manufacturer</option>
              <option>model</option>
              <option>description</option>
              <option>cost</option>
              <option>tags</option>
              <option>url</option>
          </select>
          <select id="tags-selectpicker" class="selectpicker" multiple>
              <option>tag</option>
              <option>description</option>
          </select>

          <button class="btn btn-primary" id="submit">
              Send your GraphQL query!
          </button>


      </div>
<br /><br /><br /><br />

<div id="graphql-container" class="text-container">

</div>


